        last_assistant_message: "All 8 repos now have `v0.1.0`. \n\n**What was fixed:**\n\n1. **CI python3 indentation bug** — Multiline python inside YAML `run: |` had indentation that became part of the Python code. Fixed by using `python3 << 'PYEOF'` heredoc (no indentation issues) with `shell: bash`.\n\n2. **Tag fallback** — CI now tries `--branch v0.1.0` first, falls back to `--branch master` if the tag doesn't exist. This makes CI resilient during development before releases.\n\n3. **Missing `gen-go` v0.1.0** — Synced and created the release. All 8 repos now have `v0.1.0`.\n\n4. **sync-repos.sh rebase retry** — Already fixed in the previous round, and it just proved itself — the gen-go push failed on first try, rebased, and succeeded on retry."
